data.enText: a natural tendency for people and animals to behave in a particular way using the knowledge and abilities that they were born with rather than thought or training

data.chText: 儿童并非生来就会分辨是非。
data.enText: Children do not know by instinct the difference between right and wrong.

data.chText: 他的本能反应就是逃跑。
data.enText: His first instinct was to run away.
Horses have a well-developed instinct for fear.

data.chText: 他早在求学时期就表现出有经商的天赋。
data.enText: Even at school, he showed he had an instinct for (= was naturally good at) business.
a feeling that makes you do sth or believe that sth is true, even though it is not based on facts or reason

simple_means.memory_skill: in 向内 + stinct 刺；刺激 → 内在的刺激 → 本能

tr: inborn pattern of behavior often responsive to specific stimuli

value.def: Instinct is the natural tendency that a person or animal has to behave or react in a particular way.

example.ex: I didn't have as strong a maternal instinct as some other mothers...
example.tran: 我不像别的母亲那样有那么强烈的母性本能。

example.ex: The basis for training relies on the dog's natural instinct to hunt and retrieve...
example.tran: 训练是基于狗搜寻和衔回的天生本能。

example.ex: He always knew what time it was, as if by instinct.
example.tran: 他总能知道几点了,仿佛是出于本能。

value.def: If you have an instinct for something, you are naturally good at it or able to do it.

example.ex: Farmers are increasingly losing touch with their instinct for managing the land...
example.tran: 农民正在逐渐丢失经营土地的本领。

example.ex: Irene is so incredibly musical and has a natural instinct to perform.
example.tran: 艾琳有着极高的音乐天分和天生的表演才能。

value.def: If it is your instinct to do something, you feel that it is right to do it.

example.ex: I should've gone with my first instinct, which was not to do the interview...
example.tran: 我本该听从自己的第一反应,不接受这次采访的。

example.ex: She hadn't followed her instinct and because of this Frank was dead.
example.tran: 她没有听从自己心里的话,弗兰克因此死了。

gramarinfo.label: usu with poss, oft N to-inf

value.def: Instinct is a feeling that you have that something is the case, rather than an opinion or idea based on facts.

example.ex: There is scientific evidence to support our instinct that being surrounded by plants is good for health...
example.tran: 我们觉得周围植物环绕会有益健康,这种直觉有科学证据支持。

example.ex: He seems so honest and genuine and my every instinct says he's not.
example.tran: 他看起来这么老实诚恳,但我的全部直觉告诉我他一点都不。

trans: (运动员或政客的)争强好胜的本能
动物本能；动物天性；动物的本能；动物踪迹；小红莓
群体本能(人或动物在行为或思维上从众的自然趋势)
